name: media_png_invalid_unknown_critical_chunk
description: |
  A deliberately invalid PNG containing an unknown critical chunk named VPAG
  between IHDR and IDAT. The chunk length is zero and the CRC is correct, so the
  failure should be specifically about the unknown critical chunk. A conforming
  decoder may ignore unknown ancillary chunks, but must reject or warn on
  unknown critical chunks because their data could be required to render the
  image correctly.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The PNG specification defines chunk naming and critical chunk handling:
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#5Chunk-naming-conventions
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "invalid-png"
  - "critical-chunk"
  - "unknown-chunk"
  - "chunk-name"
---
